  "prompt": "I've only heard one song by Jackson Browne which I totally loved! 'Late for the sky'! Can anyone recommend me more Jackson Browne songs? Even albums?",
  "response": "\"Late for the Sky\" is indeed a classic track by Jackson Browne! If you enjoyed that song, you're in for a treat with more of his work. Here are some song recommendations and albums you might enjoy:\n\n### Songs:\n1. **\"Running on Empty\"** - A quintessential Jackson Browne track that's both introspective and energetic.\n2. **\"The Pretender\"** - A powerful song reflecting on life and societal pressures.\n3. **\"Doctor My Eyes\"** - One of his earliest hits, with a catchy melody and profound lyrics.\n4. **\"These Days\"** - A beautifully melancholic song that showcases Browne's songwriting prowess.\n5. **\"For a Dancer\"** - A touching tribute to a friend, with evocative lyrics and a gentle melody.\n\n### Albums:\n1. **\"Running on Empty\" (1977)** - This live album is often considered one of Browne's best works, featuring songs like the titular track and \"Stay.\"\n2. **\"The Pretender\" (1976)** - This album delves into themes of disillusionment and hope, with standout tracks like \"The Pretender\" and \"Here Come Those Tears Again.\"\n3. **\"For Everyman\" (1973)** - This album contains classics like \"These Days\" and \"Take It Easy,\" which he co-wrote with Glenn Frey of the Eagles.\n4. **\"Jackson Browne\" (1972)** - His debut album, featuring \"Doctor My Eyes\" and \"Rock Me on the Water,\" is a great introduction to his early work.\n5. **\"Hold Out\" (1980)** - Features popular songs like \"Boulevard\" and showcases Browne's evolution as an artist.\n\n### Additional Recommendations:\n- If you're interested in deeper cuts and lesser-known gems, check out **\"Farther On\"** from \"The Pretender\" and **\"Song for Adam\"** from \"Jackson Browne.\"\n- For a more recent taste of Browne's work, you might enjoy **\"The Dreamer\"** from his 2014 album \"Standing in the Breach.\"\n\nJackson Browne's discography is rich and varied, so these recommendations should give you a good starting point. Enjoy exploring his music!",
